/najmabadi.htm\">\"Archived copy\"</a>. Archived from <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.fas.harvard.edu/womenstudy/najmabadi.htm\">the original</a> on 2007-10-13<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2007-10-13</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Archived+copy&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.fas.harvard.edu%2Fwomenstudy%2Fnajmabadi.htm&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AAfsaneh+Najmabadi\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_links\">External links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Afsaneh_Najmabadi&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: External links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li>Encyclopaedia of Women and Islamic Cultures (EWIC), University of California, Davis (<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://sjoseph.ucdavis.edu/ewic/index.htm\">Home page</a>), (<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://sjoseph.ucdavis.edu/ewic/other/EWIC_TOC.htm\">Tables of Contents, Volumes I-VI</a>).</li>\n<li>Beth Potier, <i>Women with mustaches, men without beards: Research illuminates the elasticity - the politics - of sexual boundaries</i>, University of Harvard Gazette, March 14, 2002. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external autonumber\" href=\"http://news.harvard.edu/gazette/2002/03.14/03-najmabadi.html\">[2]</a></li></ul>\n<div role=\"navigation\" class=\"navbox\" aria-labelledby=\"Authority_control_frameless_&amp;#124;text-top_&amp;#124;10px_&amp;#124;alt=Edit_this_at_Wikidata_&amp;#124;link=https&amp;#58;//www.wikidata.org/wiki/Q4690366&amp;#124;Edit_this_at_Wikidata\" style=\"padding:3px\"><table class=\"nowraplinks hlist navb